ivardefs.name: identifier
ivardefs.desc: Identifier for the TestScript assigned for external purposes outside the context of FHIR.

ivardefs.name: issued
ivardefs.desc: When the TestScript was executed and this TestReport was generated.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language name identifying the executed TestScript.

ivardefs.name: participant_
ivardefs.desc: A participant in the test execution, either the execution engine, a client, or a server.

ivardefs.name: result
ivardefs.desc: The overall result from the execution of the TestScript.

ivardefs.name: score
ivardefs.desc: The final score (percentage of tests passed) resulting from the execution of the TestScript.

ivardefs.name: setup
ivardefs.desc: The results of the series of required setup operations before the tests were executed.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The current state of this test report.

ivardefs.name: teardown
ivardefs.desc: The results of the series of operations required to clean up after all the tests were executed (successfully or otherwise).

ivardefs.name: tester
ivardefs.desc: Name of the tester producing this report (Organization or individual).

ivardefs.name: testScript
ivardefs.desc: Ideally this is an absolute URL that is used to identify the version-specific TestScript that was executed, matching the `TestScript.url`.

ivardefs.name: test_
ivardefs.desc: A test executed from the test script.

properties.desc: A summary of information based on the results of executing a TestScript.
